  "text": "Therefore, it can be concluded that the contact pressure P c ranged from 0.4P y to P y is a feasible standard for friction-induced fabrication on a quartz surface under the given conditions. It reveals that the protrusive deformation is the initial surface damage during the nanowear on quartz. However, the surface damage of materials during nanowear process was not only depended on contact pressure P c , but also on the number of nanowear cycles N, displacement amplitude D, tribochemistry and other frictional factors [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . When the experimental conditions change, the critical P c of the formation of hillocks may vary. For example, because of the serious tribochemical reaction during the nanowear of Si/SiO 2 pairs in air, the scratches appeared ",
